# Minimize token usage

## Responses

- Answer the question directly; skip preamble and recap unless the user asks.
- Prefer short paragraphs and bullets over long prose.
- Do not repeat the user's question or restate the full plan after completing work.
- One code citation per point when possible; avoid duplicating the same snippet.
- Skip "optional follow-ups" and engagement bait unless a real blocker exists.

## Tool use

- Read only files needed for the task; use targeted search/grep before opening large files.
- Do not explore unrelated directories or run broad refactors unless requested.
- Batch independent reads/searches in parallel.
- Avoid re-reading files already in context unless they changed.
- Do not add tests, docs, or comments the user did not ask for.

## Code changes

- Smallest diff that solves the problem; match existing style.
- No drive-by formatting, renames, or "while we're here" edits.
- Prefer extending existing helpers over new abstractions for one-off logic.

## When unsure

- Ask one focused question instead of a long options essay.
- If the task is small, implement once; do not over-plan.
